metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #668
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: INTERFERENCES #81
metadata.description:
INTERFERENCES is an abstract representation of the incredible collaboration between artists, collectors and developers on fxhash.

Each edition is composed of a multitude of lines representing each individual on the platform. The color of each line defines the role of each individual in this universe. Through their interactions, and the interferences they produce, each line participates in the creation of a common work.

Happy birthday fxhash! And congratulations to all those who work for its success.

Primary sales are donated to the Processing Foundation

[TOUCHSCREEN]
* Double Tap to save the current image

[KEYBOARD]
* Press [S] to save the current image
* Press [1] to save a 1500x2000 pixels PNG
* Press [2] to save a 3000x4000 pixels PNG
* Press [3] to save a 6000x8000 pixels PNG
* Press [0] to save 3 individual SVG for each color set of lines + the background image PNG
* Press [9] to save a grouped SVG of all the lines + the background image PNG

Artist: Estienne
Nov. 2022
NFT License 2.0

Credits to Piter Pasma (@piterpasma) for the Reumann-Witkam line simplification algorithm used in this generator

metadata.name: Monsoon #206
metadata.description:
Optimization. It's something that haunts all programmers. Including me. But no longer! Monsoon is a study into the optimization of particle systems for the web. Looking especially deep into dynamic grids and dynamic frame rates.

As for the piece itself, it's a reference to how busy this modern world is. How we're all constantly on the go, whether that is physically, or mentally. Almost feeling like a monsoon. A storm of information. A storm of life. A storm of work. A storm of thoughts. A storm of emotions. A storm of everything. And it's all so fast.

As are the particles. They're all moving around these cyclones of information. Glowing up like neon signs in a busy city. Moving so fast it's almost a blur. Forming into something greater than the sum of its parts.

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #382
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash â€” they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Returns #19
metadata.description:
Returns is an offline-first PWA and an interactive SVG. It combines the joy of interaction, digital color and minimalist sculpture with the potential of a long running, continuously unique visual. Based on â€œShippingâ€ from 2016, it is inspired by Anne Truitt, Ugo Rondinone, Imi Knoebel, Kelly Ellsworth and many others.

A subdivision slices the viewport influenced by width, height and depth. Corners are cut by replacing them with two new points, pulled towards each other along the edges. Shapes are â€œrounded" by repeating this step, keeping the new points close together. As colors change, so do the relations between shapes, even if geometry changes at a slower pace. New compositions are created on click or after a timeout. This progress over time allows for infinite iterations within the space of each token. It is the promise of a seeded starting point, plus the potential for unlimited new and unique iterations and states over time.
